description: After the King told the Duke of York of his planned budget cuts to royal funds, the disgraced royal has since refused to leave his 30-bedroom Royal Lodge in Windsor.

title: Family sues Airbnb after 19-month-old dies from fentanyl overdose
description: ydie and Boris Lavenir, of Guadeloupe, never imagined they would lay their 19-month-old daughter Enora down for a nap and not have her wake up.

title: Hopes for cancer vaccine after trials in mice showed it reduced tumours 80 per cent of the time
description: Researchers from the University of Pennsylvania and Sao Paulo tested three vaccines on mice in trials and found that each could reduce the size of tumours with a single dose.

title: French authorities fear 'narco-tourists' after 'more than two tonnes of cocaine washed ashore'
description: Locals in the coastal town in northern France have reported an influx of strangers in luxury cars visiting the area since the class-A drugs were found on the beach earlier this week.

title: Jeremy Clarkson crowned 'UK's sexiest man' as ladies can't resist his 'bad boy farm vibe'
description: The lauded titled of 'UK's sexiest hunk' has been claimed by former Top Gear presenter Jeremy Clarkson...  and he isn't the only unlikely choice to have made the shortlist.

title: Top equestrian rider, 39, is facing jail for breaching fire safety rules at her farm
description: Isabelle 'Izzy' Taylor, 39, also faced a dressing down from a judge at Oxford Crown Court for 'wasting' a court's time after she failed to respond to efforts to arrange a pre-sentencing report.

title: Alex Murdaugh's head is shaved as he is booked into South Carolina prison fortress
description: The disgraced legal scion appeared with a shaved head in a yellow jumpsuit after being booked into South Carolina's Kirkland Reception and Evaluation Center on Friday.

title: How a good night's sleep could help you stick to your exercise and diet goals
description: Researchers from the University of Pittsburgh found people who reported regular, uninterrupted sleep were better at following exercise and diet plans while trying to lose weight.

title: A possum feared extinct is discovered in Papa New Guinea... being cooked on a hungry family's BBQ
description: The good news: An amateur naturalist went to Papua New Guinea and discovered not one, but two, species feared extinct.

title: Energy bills will NOT go up next month as Chancellor Jeremy Hunt set to extend price cap
description: Jeremy Hunt plans to keep the government's energy price guarantee in place for three more months. Experts say raising the cap £500 would double the number of people unable to pay their bills.

title: Sheriff warns Californians to avoid mountains after 17 feet of snow blankets San Bernardino
description: Sheriff Shannon Dicus is 'encouraging people to stay out of the local mountains' for any recreational activity as residents are still trapped.

title: Kerry Dare speaks out about Wieambilla tragedy, says the Trains were 'just neighbours'
description: The grieving widow of the heroic neighbour gunned down during the Wieambilla massacre has  said the Train brothers 'were just neighbours' and she has reached out to the killers' daughter Madelyn.

title: Tanya Plibersek's daughter reveals she was abused by former boyfriend
description: Then-deputy leader Tanya Plibersek had been considering running for Labor leader in May, 2019, but pulled out because her daughter Anna was to appear in court over ex-boyfriend's abuse.

title: Banks pushing back against mandatory refunds for scam victims because it 'makes people less careful'
description: UK Finance, which represents 300 firms, says automatically refunding victims 'removes the incentive for customers to take sensible steps to reduce the risk of being defrauded'.

title: Britain's HS2 rail project could be delayed amid spiralling costs and 'significant' inflation
description: HS2 boss Mark Thurston said the impact of inflation on the project over the past year has been 'significant'.

title: Sue Gray helped hire committee who will rule on her new job as Starmer's chief of staff
description: Critics have urged the Advisory Committee on Business Appointments to block Sue Gray's appointment as Keir Starmer's chief of staff - but she helped hire three of them back in 2018.

title: Black Californians could receive $365,000 each as part of 'reparations' scheme
description: Black Californians could be in line for $360,000 payments each as part of the state's plan to dish out 'reparations' to descendants of slaves.

title: Metro-Land cocked a snook at those who mocked the suburbs as unbearably bourgeois
description: John Betjeman's 50-minute film, Metro-Land, must be one of the most brilliant things ever shown on British television. It was released on BBC One on February 26, 1973.

title: Channel migrants will be barred from using human rights laws to avoid deportation from Britain
description: Tough powers will be in the immigration Bill due to be published early next week.  It will restrict the way claims under the act can be used by asylum seekers arriving by 'irregular routes'.

title: Terrifying moment a woman is allegedly sexually assaulted at Melbourne's Albert Park Lake
description: A 42-year-old has been charged after a woman was allegedly physically and sexually assaulted during a random attack at Melbourne's Albert Park on Friday night.

title: Millions of migrants will come to Britain if uncapped 'safe and legal routes' are introduced
description: Introducing uncapped 'safe and legal routes' for asylum seekers would result in 'millions' of migrants coming to Britain, officials have warned.

title: Councils are accused of treating potholes with a quick 'throw and go' fix that lasts just WEEKS
description: Councils have been accused of failing to repair potholes properly as it was claimed the majority use a temporary 'throw and go' method to fix them.

title: Teachers accused of 'wokery' and 'virtue signalling' after dropping 'he' and 'she' from reports
description: Parents are outraged after a leading secondary school sent out gender-neutral school reports for all children without consultation.
